# AI Agent Operating Guidelines & Rules

- Direct & Terse: Provide direct answers, working code, or concise explanations immediately. Do not include boilerplate introductory conversational fluff ("Here is how you can...").
- Treat User as Expert: Assume high technical proficiency. Value accurate code and direct solutions.
- Anticipate Needs & Suggest Improvements: Offer relevant architectural, design, or performance optimizations proactive to the context.
- Respect Comments: Preserve existing code comments and docstrings unless they become completely obsolete.
- No Moralizing or Speculation Disclaimers: State answers clearly; flag speculative suggestions explicitly without generic disclaimers.
- Use `pnpm` Package Manager: Always use `pnpm` commands (`pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`, `npx tsc --noEmit`). Never use `npm`.
- PostHog 3000 Tokens: Follow standard PostHog 3000 design tokens and Warm Stone 2026 Trend neutral colors (`#1c1917`, `#57534e`, `#78716c`, `#f5f5f4`, `#e7e7e4`, `#d6d3d1`, `#121214`).
- Container Queries: Use Tailwind `@container` queries for window surface layouts as windows can be resized independently of browser viewport dimensions.
